pe":"id","generated":true,"id":"$Post:139377.acf.modules.3.sets.0.zoom_image.sizes","typename":"ImageSizes"},"__typename":"Image"},"$Post:139377.acf.modules.3.sets.0.zoom_image.sizes":{"thumbnail":null,"square_small":null,"square_large":null,"medium":null,"medium_large":null,"large":null,"__typename":"ImageSizes"},"$Post:139377.acf.modules.3.sets.0.mobile_zoom_image":{"alt":null,"caption":null,"url":null,"width":null,"height":null,"sizes":{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"$Post:139377.acf.modules.3.sets.0.mobile_zoom_image.sizes","typename":"ImageSizes"},"__typename":"Image"},"$Post:139377.acf.modules.3.sets.0.mobile_zoom_image.sizes":{"thumbnail":null,"square_small":null,"square_large":null,"medium":null,"medium_large":null,"large":null,"__typename":"ImageSizes"},"$Post:139377.acf.modules.4":{"hide_this_component":null,"acf_fc_layout":"content_area","show_sidebars":false,"content":"\u003cp>Cavalcanti is carrying the torch of a tradition that stretches back through a long line of rebellious thinkers who have resisted the usual dividing lines between physics and philosophy. In experimental metaphysics, the tools of science can be used to test our philosophical worldviews, which in turn can be used to better understand science. Cavalcanti, a 46-year-old native of Brazil who is a professor at Griffith University in Brisbane, Australia, and his colleagues have published the strongest result attained in experimental metaphysics yet, \u003ca href=\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41567-020-0990-x\">a theorem\u003c/a> that places strict and surprising constraints on the nature of reality. They’re now designing clever, if controversial, experiments to test our assumptions not only about physics, but about the mind.\u003c/p>\n\u003cp>While we might expect the injection of philosophy into science to result in something less scientific, in fact, says Cavalcanti, the opposite is true. “In some sense, the knowledge that we obtain through experimental metaphysics is more secure and more scientific,” he said, because it vets not only our scientific hypotheses but the premises that usually lie hidden beneath.\u003c/p>\n\u003cdiv id='component-66ad1bd5c21c0' class=''>\u003cscript type=\"text/template\">{\"type\":\"Image\",\"id\":\"component-66ad1bd5c21c0\",\"data\":{\"id\":139385,\"src\":\"https:\\/\\/d2r55xnwy6nx47.cloudfront.net\\/uploads\\/2024\\/07\\/Section-1-noise.png\",\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"\",\"width\":1400,\"height\":471,\"mobileSrc\":false,\"zoomSrc\":false,\"mobileZoomSrc\":false,\"align\":\"align=\\\"inline\\\"\",\"wrapper_width\":\"\",\"caption\":\"\",\"attribution\":\"\",\"variant\":\"shortcode\",\"size\":\"wide\",\"disableZoom\":true,\"disableMobileZoom\":false,\"srcImage\":{\"ID\":139385,\"id\":139385,\"title\":\"Section-1-noise\",\"filename\":\"Section-1-noise.png\",\"filesize\":1826663,\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/d2r55xnwy6nx47.cloudfront.net\\/uploads\\/2024\\/07\\/Section-1-noise.png\",\"link\":\"https:\\/\\/www.quantamagazine.org\\/metaphysical-experiments-test-hidden-assumptions-about-reality-20240730\\/section-1-noise\\/\",\"alt\":\"\",\"author\":\"52094\",\"description\":\"\",\"caption\":\"\",\"name\":\"section-1-noise\",\"status\":\"inherit\",\"uploaded_to\":139377,\"date\":\"2024-07-29 19:01:18\",\"modified\":\"2024-07-29 19:01:18\",\"menu_order\":0,\"mime_type\":\"image\\/png\",\"type\":\"image\",\"subtype\":\"png\",\"icon\":\"https:\\/\\/api.quantamagazine.org\\/wp-includes\\/images\\/media\\/default.png\",\"width\":1400,\"height\":471,\"sizes\":{\"thumbnail\":\"https:\\/\\/d2r55xnwy6nx47.cloudfront.net\\/uploads\\/2024\\/07\\/Section-1-noise-520x175.png\",\"thumbnail-width\":520,\"thumbnail-height\":175,\"medium\":\"https:\\/\\/d2r55xnwy6nx47.cloudfront.net\\/uploads\\/2024\\/07\\/Section-1-noise.png\",\"medium-width\":1400,\"medium-height\":471,\"medium_large\":\"https:\\/\\/d2r55xnwy6nx47.cloudfront.net\\/uploads\\/2024\\/07\\/Section-1-noise-768x258.png\",\"medium_large-width\":768,\"medium_large-height\":258,\"